# Storefront UI: Shadcn + Tailwind

The storefront uses **Shadcn UI** (Radix primitives + Tailwind) and **Tailwind CSS**.

## UI Components Location

- **Shadcn components**: `storefront/src/components/ui/`
- **Utility**: `storefront/src/lib/utils.ts` (`cn()` for class merging)
- **Theme / design tokens**: `storefront/src/styles/globals.css` (CSS variables: `--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`, etc.)

## Available Shadcn Components

| Component   | Path                         | Use for                          |
|------------|------------------------------|----------------------------------|
| Accordion  | `@/components/ui/accordion`  | Collapsible sections (FAQ, tabs)|
| Badge      | `@/components/ui/badge`      | Counts, status, tags             |
| Button     | `@/components/ui/button`     | Actions, triggers                |
| Card       | `@/components/ui/card`      | Product cards, content blocks    |
| Checkbox   | `@/components/ui/checkbox`    | Filters, forms                   |
| Dialog     | `@/components/ui/dialog`     | Modals, overlays                 |
| Input      | `@/components/ui/input`      | Text fields                      |
| Label      | `@/components/ui/label`       | Form labels                      |
| Rating     | `@/components/ui/rating`     | Star rating (read-only or input) |
| Select     | `@/components/ui/select`     | Dropdowns                        |
| Separator  | `@/components/ui/separator`   | Dividers                         |
| Skeleton   | `@/components/ui/skeleton`   | Loading placeholders             |
| Slider     | `@/components/ui/slider`     | Range inputs (e.g. price filter) |
| Sonner     | `@/components/ui/sonner`     | Toaster; use `toast()` from `sonner` |

## When to Use Shadcn vs Tailwind

### ✅ Use Shadcn (`@/components/ui/*`) For:
- **Forms**: Input, Label, Checkbox, Select, Slider
- **Overlays**: Dialog
- **Feedback**: Button, Badge, Skeleton, Sonner (toast)
- **Layout**: Card, Separator, Accordion
- **Rating**: `@/components/ui/rating` (custom star rating)

### ✅ Use Tailwind For:
- Layout, spacing, flexbox, grid
- One-off styles, responsive breakpoints
- Color utilities, typography (unless using theme tokens)

### ✅ Icons
Use **lucide-react** for icons (e.g. `ShoppingCart`, `ChevronDown`, `Loader2`, `X`, `Bell`).

